Definition: in a dispirited manner without hope
Example: the first Mozartian opera to be subjected to this curious treatment ran dispiritedly for five performances
Synonyms: adj, all, dejected, dispirited, hopelessly, hopeless, in, a, manner, without, hope, the, first, Mozartian, opera, to, be, subjected, this, curious, treatment, ran, for, five, performances
Category: adv.all
